{
  "stem": "25591.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother taught me to always do the right thing, and I didn't know what the right thing was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was another huge black sailor, and I said, what's the deal?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Can you take an orange, or can you take a banana?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Can you make your own choice?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he looked at me and he said, man, you eat all the goddamn bananas and all the goddamn oranges you want.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I knew I was in paradise.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I arrived in New York, and a very nice lady waited for me, and I went home to her house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The next day, they took me to see the Rockettes at-- at New York City, and then they put me on the train.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In Chicago, where I changed trains, I met the head of B'nai B'rith Hilal at the time, who subsequently became president of Brandeis University, Abe Sachar, and his wonderful secretary, Marilyn, who basically picked me on the basis of my papers, so I thanked them.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I have to jump ahead because this is interesting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was in 1947.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was told by Marilyn that in 1980, that's '57, '67, 33 years later, she had a trip to San Francisco, vacation trip.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she got off the plane and took a cab to the city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a gigantic billboard with my picture and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the suggestion vote for Tom Lantos, Democrat, Congress.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she thought it was a dream.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she called-- she tracked down my campaign headquarters, and she said, is this the Tom Lantos who came?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this is how she found out what happened to the boy she picked in 1947 to get a scholarship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was running for Congress.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
